    <feedback>
      MAJOR INCONSISTENCY: Remedy's physical description and manifestation. The character card (line 71-72) states 'Remedy appears as mushrooms of various types, sizes, and colors depending on purpose. Medicinal mushrooms tend to be small, pale, with gilled undersides. Fruiting bodies can emerge within 20 minutes to several hours. Each mushroom is temporary, decomposing back after serving its purpose. When using the robot: one of the two salvaged robots, patched together from various human technology, about 1.5 meters tall, humanoid shape with articulated arms and basic manipulation capabilities.'

      However, in Medical Treatment passage (line 12): 'Small pale clusters emerge from the soil-covered floor, pushing up through the groundcover in accelerated time-lapse. Within minutes, they've fruited fully' - this suggests mushrooms fruit in MINUTES, not '20 minutes to several hours' as specified in the character card.

      More critically, the character card says there are TWO salvaged robots total in the facility, with Remedy controlling ONE of them. But nowhere in the story is there any mention of what happened to the second robot, who controls it, or why only Remedy gets robot access. This is a significant world-building gap - if there are two robots, the other one needs to be accounted for (is it broken? controlled by someone else? stored somewhere?). This becomes especially problematic during action scenes where additional hands/mobility would be useful.
    </feedback>
    <reason>Fixed robot count (one not two), clarified mushroom timing</reason>
