    <feedback>
      ABILITY INCONSISTENCY: Remedy's chemical production capabilities are inconsistent across combat scenes.

      In Attack Begins (line 29): 'Remedy spreads toward the western breach, releasing clouds of something that smells sharp and chemical.' Later (line 67-76): Remedy deploys chemical clouds that react with hostile spore clouds, creating neutralization reactions and toxic sludge. Line 143: 'Remedy deploys more defensive chemicals but they're running low. You can only produce so many compounds before exhausting your resources.'

      However, in Together Not Just Coordinated (line 11-12): 'Remedy positions near the gaps between layers one and two—chemical traps ready.' Then successfully deploys chemicals multiple times throughout the extended battle without apparent resource limitations until very late in the fight.

      The character card (line 37-38) mentions as a FLAW: 'Sometimes too focused on immediate chemical solutions, missing social or emotional dimensions of problems. Can be impatient with protocol and bureaucracy even when it serves a purpose. Makes mistakes with mushroom properties—not all the medicinal varieties work as intended, some have unexpected side effects, occasionally grows the wrong compound entirely.'

      Yet in BOTH battle scenes, Remedy's chemistry works perfectly every time. No mention of unexpected side effects, wrong compounds, or mistakes. This is a significant character flaw that should manifest under pressure - the character card explicitly says they make mistakes with compounds, but in actual combat situations (high pressure, rapid deployment), everything works exactly as intended. This undermines the established character trait and makes Remedy too competent/perfect in their specialty.
    </feedback>
    <reason>Added chemical mistake in combat - wrong compound accelerates dissolution</reason>
